4) Outline five (5) current HIV/AIDS prevention strategies in Kenya
i) Health education - emphasis of prevention and adherence to treatment
ii) Abstinence and safe sex practices - reduce incidence and acquisition of new strains among the infected
iii) Behaviour changes modification - sexual behaviour - partners,
iv) Treatment - early treatment, adherence, early treatment of STIs
v) Distribution of condoms - institutions, bars, recreation centres
vi) Use of clean syringes and needles - facilities, drug users
vii) Exchanges programs - sharing of experiences on control, positive living, success stories
viii) Anti-retroviral treatment - improve quality of life through reduced of opportunistic infections
ix) Counselling and adolescence services - encourage behaviour changes (any 5-2 marks each)

